title: Wall Street Healthy? Froot Loops Healthy? 3.10.20
itunes:title: Wall Street Healthy? Froot Loops Healthy? 3.10.20
description:
In episode 586, Jack and Miles are joined by comedian James Heaney to discuss coronavirus updates, the stock market, senators' self-quarantining themselves, top cereals ranked, how corporate companies are celebrating International Women's Day, festivals being canceled, and more!

FOOTNOTES:

  1. Coronavirus updates live: World markets tumble and all of Italy goes on lockdown
  2. Stock market news live: Oil crashes, stocks crater on coronavirus, crude war fears
  3. Exclusive: The Strongest Evidence Yet That America Is Botching Coronavirus Testing
  4. Sen. Ted Cruz and Rep. Paul Gosar will self-quarantine after interacting with individual with coronavirus
  5. Italy’s Draconian Lockdown Shows Why Mass Quarantines Won’t Work in the West
  6. Your favorite childhood cereals, ranked by sugar
  7. Apple Gathers an Incredible Cast for Its International Women's Day Ad
  8. Apple’s credit card is being investigated for discriminating against women
  9. Things We Saw Today: Shell Gas Station Attempts to Celebrate International Women’s Day by Becoming “She’ll”
  10. After Being Harassed And Pushed Out Of A Shell Oil Refinery, This Woman Pushed Back
  11. International Women's Day risks becoming 'corporate Mother's Day', feminists say
  12. COACHELLA FATE UNCERTAIN AMID PUBLIC EMERGENCY ... 1st Coronavirus Case
  13. The Cost of Canceling SXSW Could Keep the Festival from Returning in 2021
  14. WATCH: Dungen - Var Har Du Varit (Official Audio)
